E.D.I.T.H. ("Even Dead, I'm The Hero")
======================================

E.D.I.T.H. is an ORIGINAL project — its own codebase. It is NOT a fork or clone of
any other agent. We study two existing open-source agents as references and, where it
genuinely helps, port specific pieces of their code with inline attribution.

References studied (both MIT-licensed):

  - Hermes Agent — Nous Research
    https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent  (MIT, Copyright (c) 2025 Nous Research)
    Studied at commit 0428945b5b07f430e23b4fc28b2bff6887477463 (2026-06-14).
    We learn from its self-improving skill loop, SQLite/FTS5 memory, sandbox backends,
    multi-provider LLM layer, and Camoufox browser approach.

  - OpenClaw — OpenClaw Foundation
    https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw  (MIT, Copyright (c) 2026 OpenClaw Foundation)
    We learn from its channel-adapter gateway pattern and Playwright/CDP browser stack.

Attribution rule: any file or function ported/adapted from either project carries an
inline comment naming the source (project + path) and its MIT license. The full reference
repositories are kept locally (outside this repo, gitignored under reference/) for study
and are never committed here.

ruflo (v3.10.x) is used only as a BUILD-TIME orchestration tool (swarm, autopilot, memory,
MCP). It is NOT a runtime dependency of E.D.I.T.H.
